# Domain — SaaS Multi-Tenant Rules

- **Tenant isolation**: every query and resource must be scoped by tenant (e.g. tenant_id)
- Never return or mutate data from another tenant
- Use middleware or dependency to resolve current tenant (e.g. from subdomain, JWT, header)
- Prefer row-level isolation (tenant_id on tables) or schema-per-tenant as per project choice
- Billing and usage must be per-tenant

Keep tenant context explicit in services and repositories; avoid implicit global tenant.
